==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Omosternum
<hw>O`mo*ster"num</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Omo-</ets>
+ <ets>sternum</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The
anterior element of the sternum which projects forward from between the
clavicles in many batrachians and is usually tipped with
cartilage.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>In many mammals, an interarticular
cartilage, or bone, between the sternum and the clavicle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Omphacine</ent>⟦br⟧
